  Copy-on-write sorted set backed by intrusive AVL tree. Same COW and
  stable-iterator design as emAvlTreeMap. Adds set algebra operators
  (+, |, -, &) and bulk Insert/Remove/Intersect with another set.

C++ usage in emCore (0 occurrences outside the header itself):
  - No usage of emAvlTreeSet found in any .h or .cpp file under include/emCore/ or src/emCore/ (other than the header's own definition and the mention in emAvlTree.h comments).

Rust equivalents found:
  - std::collections::HashSet used in src/emCore/emInputState.rs:11 (for pressed keys)
  - std::collections::BTreeSet used in src/emCore/emImage.rs:1
  - No direct port of emAvlTreeSet exists or is needed — it has zero usage in emCore

Coverage gaps:
  - Set algebra operators (+, |, -, &) — HashSet/BTreeSet provide equivalent via std traits
  - Ordered access (GetFirst, GetLast, GetNearest*) — BTreeSet provides ordered iteration; HashSet does not
  - Copy-on-write / stable iterators — not replicated in Rust
  - No gap is actionable since emAvlTreeSet has zero usage in emCore

